","position":{"commit_sha":"1bb959531dfd1626e09c4f37cb32458810b612b4","position":"1784844856999100001-30a72172-b163-4523-a18a-dc8a818cd2ab"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"2029d9a81737dbef910b597653168479872c7423b37e45f41208f630fc94fb40","event_uuid":"5a8785bc-ee2c-4fd4-8a26-ab9760b744ab","position":{"commit_sha":"94b43faa402d85e807e6c1b73920f9d3cc082a65","position":"1784846016154213001-5a8785bc-ee2c-4fd4-8a26-ab9760b744ab"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-218_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"cbe2d483-8609-4f4e-ba56-db538f86808d","comments":[],"created_at":1784820313309860001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[],"description":"## Context / Problem\n\nTwo backend-neutral core modules load Jira rich-text/limit modules by literal lazy-load key\nand run them unconditionally — for ANY configured backend:\n\n- `outbound_comments.py:68` (`_ADF_KEY = \"rebar_reconciler.adapters.jira.adf\"`, loaded at\n  `:75-85`) and `outbound_comments.py:71` (`_COMMENT_LIMITS_KEY =\n  \"rebar_reconciler.adapters.jira.comment_limits\"`, loaded at `:88`) — comment-body\n  formatting/truncation on the outbound comment-diff path.\n- `inbound_translate.py:315` (`_ADF_KEY_APPLIER`, loaded at `:319-324`) —\n  `_normalize_adf_body` decodes a raw ADF dict to text as defense-in-depth on the inbound\n  apply path (bug 1bb2-5da5).\n\nA GitHub/Linear backend would still have its comments ADF-encoded and Jira-limit-truncated.\nThese literal keys are the last vendor reach-through in neutral core paths after the sibling\nstories land; epic bbf1's separation goal (\"a second backend drops in behind the port\")\nrequires them behind the port.\n\n## Approach\n\nRoute both modules through the port roles that already own these responsibilities:\n\n- `FieldSanitizer` (already pinned in `_backend.py` as the vendor hard-limit defense, with the\n  existing SEND-side `sanitize_comment(body: str) -> str`, which truncates AND logs a warning)\n  gains ONE new method, `fit_comment(body: str) -> str` — a PURE fit-to-limit for the\n  comment-DIFF comparison path (`outbound_comments.py:324`), delegating to\n  `adapters/jira/comment_limits.py`'s `truncate_comment_body` with NO warning (the compare\n  path must not emit send-side warnings). `fit_comment` is the single, consistently-named\n  comment-fit surface used throughout this plan; `adapters/jira/adf.py` provides only the\n  DECODE (`adf_to_text`), which is served by `InboundMapper.normalize_rich_text` (below), NOT\n  by the fit surface.\n  `outbound_comments.py` resolves the configured backend's sanitizer via the registry seam\n  (`select_backend(load_config())` — pattern proven at `outbound_differ.py:450-454`) instead\n  of lazy-loading vendor modules, and the two literal keys at `outbound_comments.py:68,71`\n  are deleted.\n- `InboundMapper` gains `normalize_rich_text(body: Any) -> str` (Jira: `adf_to_text` for\n  dicts, identity for strings — exactly today's `_normalize_adf_body`,\n  `inbound_translate.py:349+`). `inbound_translate.py` calls the backend's inbound mapper;\n  the literal key at `inbound_translate.py:315` is deleted. The defense-in-depth property\n  (a raw vendor rich-text dict on the wire never reaches an EDIT event's `description`) is\n  preserved backend-neutrally.\n- Add a sweep case to `tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/test_backend_neutrality.py`: no\n  package-root core module contains the literal string `\"rebar_reconciler.adapters.jira\"`,\n  with a single recorded exemption for `inbound_fields.py:24` — that module IS the Jira\n  `InboundMapper` implementation (delegated by `adapters/jira/backend.py:43-47`) that\n  remains at the package root only for loader location-pinning reasons; its physical\n  relocation is out of this epic's scope and tracked by follow-up ticket\n  `556a-5a1f-adb3-4139` (linked `discovered_from` epic bbf1).\n\nRejected alternatives: (a) a new sixth role Protocol (\"RichTextCodec\") — YAGNI: FieldSanitizer\nalready owns vendor-limit defense per its `_backend.py` docstring and InboundMapper already\nowns vendor→local payload translation; fewer than 3 call sites for a new role. (b) Leaving\nthe lazy keys because \"they are only strings, not imports\" — the loader still executes vendor\ncode on neutral paths for any backend, which is the substance of the leak.\n\n## Scope\n\n- src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/_backend.py (FieldSanitizer comment-fit surface; InboundMapper.normalize_rich_text)\n- src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/outbound_comments.py (route via sanitizer; delete both literal keys)\n- src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/inbound_translate.py (route via inbound mapper; delete the literal key)\n- src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/adapters/jira/backend.py (implement the new members, delegating to adf/comment_limits)\n- src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/inbound_fields.py (Jira mapper: normalize_rich_text implementation)\n- tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/test_backend_neutrality.py (literal-key sweep with the recorded inbound_fields.py exemption)\n- tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/ (comment formatting/truncation + normalize_rich_text behavior tests)\n\n## Testing\n\n- Happy path: an outbound comment body formats and truncates byte-identically to today via\n  the sanitizer route; a plain-string inbound description passes through\n  `normalize_rich_text` unchanged.\n- Failure/edge: an over-limit comment truncates with today's marker semantics; a raw ADF dict\n  arriving on the inbound apply path is decoded to text and never written verbatim into an\n  EDIT event (the bug 1bb2-5da5 regression case, now backend-neutral).\n- Gate: the sweep case fails when any package-root core module (except the recorded\n  `inbound_fields.py` exemption) contains the `\"rebar_reconciler.adapters.jira\"` literal.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `outbound_comments.py` and `inbound_translate.py` contain neither `adapters.jira`\n      imports nor `\"rebar_reconciler.adapters.jira\"` lazy-key literals — verified by the new\n      sweep case in `tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/test_backend_neutrality.py`.\n- [ ] Comment formatting/truncation and inbound rich-text normalization behave identically\n      for Jira — verified by the behavior tests in Testing (including the 1bb2-5da5\n      regression case).\n- [ ] The sweep gate documents the single `inbound_fields.py` exemption with its rationale\n      and the follow-up ticket id — verified by reading the gate test.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` green; whole test tree collects with 0 errors.\n\n## Plan-review remediation (drift re-review, G1G2 findings)\n\nThree under-scoped consumer surfaces are pinned here so no lazy-key deletion orphans a caller:\n\n1. **Outbound-comment ADF DECODE (`outbound_comments.py:134`).** `_normalize_comment_body`\n   calls `adf.adf_to_text(body)` to DECODE a remote Jira ADF comment dict to comparable text on\n   the comment-DIFF path (bug 85a1) — a decode, not a send-side fit/truncate. It routes through\n   the backend's `InboundMapper.normalize_rich_text(body)` (the SAME decode surface as the\n   inbound apply path: `adf_to_text` for dicts, identity for strings). `normalize_rich_text`\n   therefore serves BOTH the inbound apply path AND this outbound comment-diff decode;\n   `FieldSanitizer.fit_comment(body)` (a pure fit-to-limit, delegating to\n   `comment_limits.truncate_comment_body`, no send-side warning) serves the `:324` compare-body\n   truncation. `outbound_comments.py` obtains BOTH the sanitizer and the inbound mapper from the\n   one `select_backend(load_config())` it resolves, and BOTH literal keys at `:68,71` are deleted.\n\n2. **`inbound_translate`'s PUBLIC decode surface (`_normalize_adf_body`).** This function is\n   re-exported by `applier.py` (`__all__` lines 322/326/361/367) and imported + called at three\n   sites by `apply_inbound_records.py` (lines 35, 145, 268, 308). It therefore STAYS as\n   inbound_translate's public function, re-implemented to route through the backend's\n   `InboundMapper.normalize_rich_text(body)` (resolved via `select_backend(load_config())`), so\n   BOTH consumers keep working unchanged and the bug-1bb2-5da5 defense (a raw ADF dict never\n   reaches an EDIT event `description`) stays intact and backend-neutral. Only the vendor\n   internals `_ADF_KEY_APPLIER` (the literal), `_AdfModule_Applier`, and `_load_adf_module` are\n   deleted from `inbound_translate.py`. Because `applier.py` re-exports those three now-deleted\n   names, `applier.py` drops them from its `inbound_translate` import list and from `__all__`\n   (keeping `_normalize_adf_body`); `apply_inbound_records.py` is untouched.\n\n3. **Scope additions:** `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/applier.py` (drop the three dead\n   re-exports; keep `_normalize_adf_body`).\n\n**AC3 restated machine-executably:** the single-`inbound_fields.py`-exemption sweep is verified\nby the test `test_no_root_core_module_carries_vendor_lazyload_literal` passing (green with\nexactly that one exemption) plus a companion `test_sweep_exemption_is_still_needed` asserting\ninbound_fields.py genuinely still carries the literal — both under `make test`, not by human\ninspection.\n\n**Added acceptance criteria:**\n- [ ] The outbound-comment ADF decode at `_normalize_comment_body:134` routes through\n      `InboundMapper.normalize_rich_text` (NOT orphaned by the `_ADF_KEY` deletion); comment-diff\n      dedup normalizes ADF-dict bodies to text byte-identically — verified by a comment-diff test\n      with an ADF-dict remote body.\n- [ ] `inbound_translate._normalize_adf_body` STAYS importable and routes through the port;\n      `applier.py` no longer imports/re-exports `_ADF_KEY_APPLIER`/`_AdfModule_Applier`/\n      `_load_adf_module`; `apply_inbound_records.py`'s three call sites behave identically\n      (ADF dict -> text) — verified by the behavior tests plus a green import of both modules.\n\n## Landed\n\nImplemented and merged to `main` as Gerrit change 936 (LLM-Review +1, Verified +1).","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/_backend.py","reason":"FieldSanitizer comment-fit surface; InboundMapper.normalize_rich_text"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/outbound_comments.py","reason":"route via sanitizer; delete both literal keys"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/inbound_translate.py","reason":"route via inbound mapper; delete the literal key"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/adapters/jira/backend.py","reason":"implement the new members"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/inbound_fields.py","reason":"normalize_rich_text implementation"},{"path":"tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/test_backend_neutrality.py","reason":"literal-key sweep with recorded exemption"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["parent","bbf1-82e1-cf9d-494a"]],"parent_id":"bbf1-82e1-cf9d-494a","parent_status_uuid":"2b6a3a75-c37f-48c8-a7a1-038eb3cde8a9","plan_review_phase":"execution","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":[],"ticket_id":"21ca-cdb4-671c-460c","ticket_type":"story","title":"Rich-text codec and comment limits behind the port: delete the adapters.jira lazy-key literals from core","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["181ab53e-86a5-4a7b-8faf-1376b3